((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13630456959', 'Dhhhhug', 1, 'Number registration fails', 'Number registration fails. Why brother creating an app and then put a complicated registration on it? Complicated in the sense it is easy for users but fails also. Glad it failed not doing business with a company like this. Don’t even download this… use excel.', '5.18.2', 'us', '2026-01-13T15:52:02-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13602207665', 'Fush47', 2, 'TLDR - There are way better options, like Monarch.', 'When Mint went EOL, I, like many others, migrated to PocketGuard. I find budgeting very difficult and Mint worked extremely well for me. I read that PocketGuard was the most similar, and they have released updates that made it more similar. UNFORTUNATELY, PocketGuard has several fundamental flaws that make it so irritating to use that I stopped using it entirely and my finances suffered as a result. I’ll start with the good. The good: you can set budgets and roll them over into the next month. This rollover feature was not an offering when I started using it, somehow. You can also now set rules to categorize transactions automatically which was not the case when I started using it; I initially had to recategorize every individual transaction if PocketGuard thought it belonged in a different budget. (This is still the case if the payment issuer name changes but I can’t really fault them for that.) The bad: one of pocketguard’s selling points is its bill tracking feature. Unfortunately, this feature is actually a drawback, as whenever PocketGuard says something is a bill, it breaks it out from your budget entirely and does not let you set a monthly budget for it. This is fine for rent, but it is utterly broken for things like quarterly water bills, when the app says “scheduled for [month]” and does not count a portion of that quarterly or yearly bill towards your monthly budget. Instead, when you hit that month, suddenly you’re completely over budget because your entire quarterly water bill or annual Strava subscription or property tax is counted towards that month alone. Many times I tried to figure out a way to make this feature work for me, but it just does not. It is also a pain for the purpose of tracking things like streaming subscriptions, because even if you set an entertainment budget and categorize Spotify as entertainment, the app then DOUBLE COUNTS that recurring payment as a) a bill and b) part of your set entertainment budget. It also does not automatically deduct recurring payments such as these from your budget so that you can easily see the actual amount you have free to spend. Most of these issues have been immediately fixed for me by moving to Monarch instead. I only wish I had done so before my annual PocketGuard subscription had pinged.', '5.18.2', 'us', '2026-01-06T09:09:44-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13598045833', 'therisle', 3, 'Debit card account', 'Hey is it possible to have my debit card automatically sync rather than me having to always approve the login on my card when I open the app?', '5.18.2', 'us', '2026-01-05T07:36:12-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13573916652', 'DaLukeSterr', 5, 'Awesome sauce', 'Awesome program. It took me about a year to get my finances sorted, but it is really helping me stick to a budget and pay off my debts. I’ve been wanting to stick to a budget for most my life and never been able to commit. But I’m finally doing it thanks to PocketGuard!!! It is very easy interface.', '5.18.2', 'us', '2025-12-30T10:55:19-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13572234252', 'justinm860', 5, 'Great support', 'I love this app. I purchased it. I hope they stick around for decades. If I ever have any questions the customer service is very attentive and quick responding.', '5.18.2', 'us', '2025-12-30T01:48:58-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13546158401', 'taggedbythuy', 5, 'Super helpful', 'Been using this app for about 3 months and I already see a difference in how I spend. It makes tracking and categorizing my purchases super easy and gives me an idea of how much I spend and on what each month. Love that it connects directly to my bank and updates every few hours. I also love the debt repayment aspect of the app. It’s keeping me on task with my goals to become debt free with a realistic timeline. I tried out maybe 3-4 other finance apps before coming back to this one. Def recommended.', '5.18.1', 'us', '2025-12-23T06:09:26-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13532457264', 'Jld1829', 5, 'It works', 'I like the multiple features and that it usually automatically syncs with my accounts (no manual tracking, except cash), the developers are responsive and quick to fix most issues, and it takes the guess work out of where my money is going. I wish you could preemptively budget in future months without having to add a reoccurring bill.', '5.18.1', 'us', '2025-12-19T13:28:57-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13529795399', 'Rising High', 1, 'Poor tech support', 'Approximately a year ago I bought a lifetime membership, and the application was satisfactory until the recent updates. Consequently, I was unable to use the application and asked to purchase Plus membership. Despite submitting multiple tickets, I have yet to receive a response. I am deeply disappointed and regret my decision to purchase the lifetime membership.', '5.18.1', 'us', '2025-12-18T20:32:23-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13527255547', 'The_devil_inside_666', 5, 'Surprised', 'App keeps getting better. Once you learn the little nuance’s to the programs it’s super easy. The latest updates make that even easier. But that’s IMO!', '5.18.1', 'us', '2025-12-18T04:38:25-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13527113847', 'Snail🐌🐌🐌🐌🐌🐌', 3, 'Have to resync every update', 'I’m finally just fed up with this app, it is so useful when it ACTUALLY WORKS unfortunately just about every time I use it I have to resync my financial accounts particularly after an app update. It takes so long that it ends up just not being worth it, I’m finding something else.', '5.18.1', 'us', '2025-12-18T03:48:34-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13526257587', 'Steve D 23', 5, 'Staying on top of all our spending', 'We have been using this for two years. I have come to depend on it to insure I spend what I intended to each month. While I do not use the budget functions I do use it to keep on top of spending totals and to insure I understand every transaction.', '5.18.1', 'us', '2025-12-17T21:11:57-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13509039818', 'Esta chiquita', 5, 'Best spending and saving manager', 'I started using PocketGuard at the suggestion of a woman I know who is excellent with money. This app has allowed me to step up and really keep track of what I’m spending and where it’s going. As a result. My finances are much healthier and I feel good about the decisions I’m making. The app has also helped me increase my credit score greatly. Thank you so much for developing this easy to use app to make money management easier for people who would prefer not to budget at all.', '5.18', 'us', '2025-12-13T07:18:03-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='949414211'), '13505639345', 'Heine Anderson', 3, 'Overall good, but the syncing issues are frustrating', 'I really don’t mind the app for what it is, but the biggest problem is when I signed up I spent a whole day categorizing the previous 2 months to what I need to see it as. And this week I went to look back and all the work I had done is gone and pretty much mis-categorized. I’m not going back to do it again. So I’m left with having to do it everyday for the current month so I can see where I’m at financially. It’ll keep some but others go back to being mid-categorized and it’s frustrating. Hope you guys can fix that so I can go back to looking at month - to - month on how much I’m spending truly against my categories that I had set up.', '5.18', 'us', '2025-12-12T09:58:52-07:00'),
