((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14097678897', 'Send Nudes 😐', 3, 'App performance falters', 'Redownloaded the app recently and my drafts are getting deleted and they delete on offload. I had to accept the new terms like 3x. It seems like you have to do things twice almost to make sure it goes through.', '461.1.0', 'us', '2026-05-23T11:07:30-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14097667740', 'danimariecaliontiktoklol', 5, 'Been my go to for over a decade', 'This is genuinely to only app I’ll use for filters on my photos. Been using since like 2015/16, with or without subscription. When I actually want to pay, the extra features are worth it. -danimarienelson / Danimariecali', '461.1.0', 'us', '2026-05-23T11:03:52-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14096529392', 'Dev ૐ', 5, 'VSCO has saved my life.', 'I am a photographer, trying to start my small business… and VSCO has given me that opportunity. Thank you VSCO, and all of the creators, for helping me make this dream a reality. Highly recommend.', '461.1.0', 'us', '2026-05-23T05:17:31-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14095469543', 'Zgpunkrockgirl', 1, 'They steal your content!', 'Please read the terms and conditions. They steal your content and sell it to train ai. It’s all right there in plain English. “License You Grant to Us. By using our Services, you grant us a royalty-free, sublicensable, non-exclusive, perpetual, irrevocable, worldwide license to use, reproduce, distribute, publicly perform, publicly display, and make derivative works of your Creator Content and Al Content (collectively, "Content"), including the name, image, voice, or likeness of any individual included in your Content, in whole or in part, and in any form, media or technology, whether now known or developed in the future. This license includes the right to use certain Content for Creator Promotion and to develop, train, and improve Al or machine learning models as further described in our Creator Content Standards. By submitting your Content to any part of our Services, you consent to us identifying you by your VSCO username (which may be a pseudonym) in connection with your Content. You waive any moral or other author''s rights you may have in connection with any of these uses of your Content.”', '461.1.0', 'us', '2026-05-22T21:54:02-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14087278249', 'da ani', 1, 'Deleting VSCO after 11 years of using it', 'I’ve loved using the VSCO app for the longest time, I remember when they came out with the premium version because they added a bunch of new features. I tried premium once and never bothered to renew because I didn’t have a need for the premium options. Now, more than half of the features (that have been there as long as been using the app) have been switched to premium only. It’s sad to see the app I’ve been able to use freely is now basically forcing me to pay $13 a month to use the same features I’ve been using for free for over 10 years.', '461.1.0', 'us', '2026-05-20T15:54:58-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14086496814', 'Addison burke', 5, 'This', 'This is an amazing app! Makes me so happy and loved! It is a way to express myself through some of my favorite picture!thank you for this!', '461.1.0', 'us', '2026-05-20T10:57:51-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14079823117', 'meridaut', 5, 'Editing and pictures', 'All the filters they have I love using for all my pictures. I love their format!', '461.1.0', 'us', '2026-05-18T14:23:35-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14074782028', '😬😭😊💃🏽🫰😳👑😬😭😊', 2, 'Frequently deletes your photos.', 'If you delete the app, photos gone. If you get a new phone, photos gone. If the app crashes all by itself and you do nothing, photos gone.', '461.1.0', 'us', '2026-05-17T06:32:48-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14073359075', 'jperson01', 1, 'Gone downhill', 'This app used to be amazing. Now it’s just like every other app obsessed with making everything about AI while putting everything behind a paywall. Time to leave this app behind.', '461.1.0', 'us', '2026-05-16T20:49:06-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14067539068', 'sbreeny', 2, 'Not Great', 'It used to be the best app to edit pics. It’s become quite heavy, very slow (to the point where it gets “stuck” saving photos and into a loop it never comes out of) plus the most expensive plan makes no sense as it adds nothing other than a couple of the same filters that are available on the cheaper version. I want to use it and love it, but I’m having a hard time finding it amazing recently and can’t wait for my subscription to expire so I can move to another option.', '461.0.0', 'us', '2026-05-15T08:16:34-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14061543249', 'Sammyjoeys', 5, 'Loveeee this app!!', 'Such a fun way to express yourself. 10/10 app!!', '461.0.0', 'us', '2026-05-13T16:19:47-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14060449728', 'MaryEmmaR', 3, 'Works well but crashes all the time.', 'I love this app when it works, but to have it crash right as I’m finishing editing a photo is extremely frustrating. It also lags and glitches anytime I edit more than a few photos in one session. I would use my Mac to prevent this, but the web browser doesn’t even have half the same tools as the app does. I get that most people edit on their phone, but if the app crashes when used on said phones, it should make complete sense to have the same tools in the web browser as a backup. Just seems like a poorly designed system, but the editing itself is fantastic. Just wish they’d fix the bugs and website', '461.0.0', 'us', '2026-05-13T09:29:34-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14050605055', 'xolanox', 3, 'Sad about the new update', 'I’ve been using the same preset edit I made back in 2018 for ALL my photos posted on socials. This new update does not allow me to use the edit because all of a sudden certain tools need a subscription to use it?! Love VSCO but it was fine before this big rebrand.', '461.0.0', 'us', '2026-05-10T15:32:22-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14050183820', 'AnnieHi89', 2, 'Coasting Downhill', 'VSCO used to be an incredible tool and platform, but in recent years its overpricing itself and adding meh features while cutting useful ones. I can make similar edits more quickly using iPhone’s built-in software and can make better edits using a tool like Lightroom. Unclear where VSCO’s value lies at $40+ annually with less and less to show for it — especially when you see how much of our data they’re apparently selling off to third parties. And note how the featured ‘most helpful’ 5-star reviews are from years ago…', '461.0.0', 'us', '2026-05-10T12:46:33-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14049631519', 'Leo Langone', 5, 'Best social media', 'Everyone is so nice and the community is wonderful. Best social media platform for sharing posts 😆', '461.0.0', 'us', '2026-05-10T09:45:27-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14044190890', 'demipsika', 3, 'The one thing I hate about VSCO', 'I love the idea of VSCO, but why isn’t there a feature where you could post photos at any time and choose the date the photo was actually taken, so your profile gallery stays in chronological order. It would make organizing your feed so much easier and fun without having to delete and repost everything just to keep your gallery in order. VSCO PLEASSEE add this feature!', '461.0.0', 'us', '2026-05-08T23:49:58-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14033275039', 'austinfromdenver', 1, 'Useless without paying', 'There are what feels like zero features on this app unless you want to pay the subscription', '461.0.0', 'us', '2026-05-05T21:45:23-07:00'),
((SELECT id FROM tracked_apps WHERE apple_id='588013838'), '14032368776', 'Pizza-Bagels-Wings', 2, 'Putting the defining feature of making a border-to-square edit behind a paywall was loser behavior', '👎🏼👎🏼👎🏼👎🏼👎🏼', '461.0.0', 'us', '2026-05-05T15:03:27-07:00'),
